args:
After the prince loses to Chronos, the masked
woman who looks like his sister Zethia is slain.
Filled with regret, the prince enlists Audric's aid
in an effort to stop Chronos's actions before
they are even allowed to begin.
I would commend you on a job well done,\nbut alas, no job has been done at all.\nI do not end.
I have no end. Only a beginning.
Now let us revisit that beginning anew!
Your struggle is futile; I am without end.\nThe battle can continue into eternity.
Your strength flags—see how you cannot\neven lift your own sword. Yield, for your\nown sake.
Dammit, you stupid body! Move! MOVE!
Vanish unto the ends of time, Auspex!
It appears we have been drawn back\nby your chain of causality.
This is my fault. It's all because I had\nto go and meddle with the past.
It's my fault she was killed!
I offer neither sympathy nor consolation.\nAs you say, your own naive decision-\nmaking invited this situation.
And with Chronos gone from this time,\nwe shall not meet again.\nFarewell, {player_name}.
Have you further business with me?
Whenever Chronos and I traveled in time,\nyou were there. Do you have some kind\nof power that allows you to follow him?
Then please take me to Chronos!\nBring me back to wherever he was\nbefore he and I first met!
I see. By defeating him at that point,\nyou hope to undo all that has transpired.

Are you certain of this course of action?
Trying once more to manipulate causality 
might well make you no different from
the Other.
I know what I'm suggesting might well be\nan affront to the goddess herself...
But I can't just sit here feeling sorry for\nmyself if there's something left to try!
He may yet be a child, but I\nsuppose he will not remain\nyoung and immature forever...
Nothing. I understand why you wish to\nundertake this plan. However, there is\na critical flaw you have not considered.
I am only able to transport MYSELF in\ntime while tracking Chronos. I cannot\nbring others along with me.
There must be something you can do!
I said the flaw was critical;\nI did not say it was fatal...
It has been some years, Cassandra.
Well, bless my stars! Never thought I'd\nlive to see the day when Au—
I'd just love to sit for a spell and jaw\nabout what's happened to you lately,\nbut I'm guessing we don't have time.
Forgive me, but such inquiries\nwill have to wait for a later day.
Do you not remember me, young man?\nLand sakes, but I remember you!\nYou're little {player_name}!
Well, I suppose it's little wonder you don't\nremember. I left the castle while you were\nstill wailing in your cradle, after all!
This is Cassandra. She was once the\nroyal court sorceress of Alberia.
When I was a baby? But she's so... Um...
Young? Oh, but you are a sweet boy to\nsay so! Now hush with all that talk and\nlet a lady have her secrets, mmm?
I remember what little crybabies you twins\nwere! Little more than wailing lungs,\nthe both of you!
Save the reminiscing for later, Cassandra.\nI need your aid in an urgent matter...
Hrm. So this dragon has the power to\nmanipulate time and change causality, eh?
I can't get into specifics, but there is a\nconnection between Chronos and I.
And because of that, I am able to go to\nwherever—and whenever—he is.\nHowever, it is a trip I can only take alone.
And you want to take the young man, yes?\nHeavens, that's but a trifle!
See, moving through time is no different\nthan moving through other worlds.
I'll just trust you on that one.
What we call ＂other worlds＂ are worlds\nof alternate possibilities.

＂What if someone somewhere did this?＂
＂What if something somewhere was that?＂
＂Other worlds＂ are the worlds of those
possibilities.
Hm. I see now.\nThat explains why I...
If I had to guess, dearie, I think Chronos\nhas the power to track down and visit\nthese alternate worlds.

So with that being the case, all you need
to do is find the world Chronos is in, then
use the space between worlds to head on
over there!
The space between worlds can be used\nlike that?
Oh, not normally! You wouldn't have\nthe foggiest idea where the place\nyou're looking for actually is.
But right now, you've got—heh—\n＂Audric＂ with you.
His connection to Chronos should allow\nhim to find the world you need.
Well, it's dynamite on paper, at least.
Okay then, Audric! Let's get ready to...\nUm, Audric?
I would ask once more about your resolve,\n{player_name}.
The world Chronos inhabits is a future that\nmay be far afield of what you expect.

You may find it difficult. You may even
see things there that are more terrible 
still than the death of your own sister.
Knowing this, would you still go?
I'd be lying if I said I'm not afraid,\nbut the chaos wrought by Chronos\nis my responsibility.
I have to make that right, no matter what\nhorrors or challenges I might face.
Please, Audric. We have to do this.
Very well. Then we will go together\nto the unimaginable future!
